    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf I try set \"prompt\" of a prompt buffer to a multi-line string, e.g\n```vim\ncall prompt_setprompt(nvim_get_current_buf(), \"abc\\ndef \")\n```\nThen the new line character is rendered as a `^%` symbol, instead of an actual new line\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. `:set buftype=prompt`\n3. `:call prompt_setprompt(nvim_get_current_buf(), \"abc\\ndef \")`\n4. `:startinsert`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe prompt should be rendered as\n```\nabc\ndef \n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-c87d92c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nYes\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKubuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkonsole 23.08.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsource",
