            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I am using prompt-buffer as chat interface with LLM, and I want to have better visual distinction between user message and LLM message. So I'm thinking of the prompt as\n```markdown\n# User\n(user message start here)\n```\nTo do that, I need \n```vim\ncall prompt_setprompt(bufnr, \"# User\\n\")\n```\n\nSo why did I submit this issue as a bug report? \n\nPreviously, Nvim prompt buffer only supported one-line user input, so one-line prompt seemed obvious. But now, Nvim supports multi-line user input, so if it only support one-line prompt, I think it should be clearly documented.",
